-- ============================================================
-- Migration 021 — Section 6 (Market Analysis) content
-- Bulk-loads M2-S6-C6 (Specialty Situations), 10 scenarios.
--
-- Difficulty distribution:
--   #1, #2  · introductory
--   #3, #4  · basic
--   #5, #6  · intermediate
--   #7, #8  · advanced
--   #9, #10 · expert
--
-- After this migration:
--   - M2-S6-C6 (Specialty Situations) has 10 of 10 scenarios loaded.
--   - Section 6 is 6 of 6 categories complete — M2-S6 is fully
--     populated (60 scenarios, 60 model_answers rows).
--
-- No schema changes. The market_indicator_analysis field type and the
-- six M2-S6 categories were created in migration 017. M2-S6-C1 was
-- loaded in migration 018; M2-S6-C2 and M2-S6-C3 in migration 019;
-- M2-S6-C4 and M2-S6-C5 in migration 020. This migration follows the
-- same pattern.
--
-- Section-level defaults from migration 017:
--   classification_options = ['Improving','Stable','Declining','Market-Dependent']
--   min_rationale_chars    = 20
--   context_labels_by_category[M2-S6-C6] = 'Specialty Context'
-- For self-describing scenario rows the per-scenario field_options_override
-- uses the more descriptive label 'Specialty Situations Context' (matching
-- the mig 019/020 pattern of expanding the section default to the full
-- category name on each scenario).
--
-- Tables array shape:
--   Where the source artifact had a single data table, it is stored as a
--   one-element 'tables' array (the convention established in 018/019).
--   Affected scenarios: #1 only.
--
--   Where the source artifact had two or more data tables with
--   GENUINELY DIFFERENT indicator sets, the migration stores them as a
--   multi-element 'tables' array, since there is no meaningful way to
--   merge non-overlapping indicator rows. This was anticipated by mig
--   018's tables-array note ('later modules use multi-element tables
--   arrays for genuinely multi-dataset scenarios') and matches the
--   mig 020 C4 #6–#10 / C5 #7 pattern.
--
--   Affected scenarios: #2 (for-sale + STR), #3 (for-sale + peak/off-season
--   STR), #4 (for-sale + STR), #5 (general + teardown submarket), #6
--   (general + redevelopment submarket), #7 (primary + ADU submarket),
--   #8 (pre-ordinance + post-ordinance STR), #9 (permanent + STR/seasonal),
--   and #10 (three-asset portfolio: lake STR / teardown / ADU — 3 tables).
--
--   No scenarios in this category match the merged-wide-cols pattern
--   (no pair of tables shares the same indicator set across two markets).
--
-- Idempotency: this migration runs once and is recorded in the
-- migration tracker by the migration runner.
-- ============================================================

BEGIN;

-- ============================================================
-- M2-S6-C6 — Specialty Situations (10 scenarios)
-- ============================================================

