"id":"str_ord","label":"STR licensing ordinance"},{"id":"rate","label":"Mortgage rate pressure"},{"id":"dock","label":"Deeded dock premium"},{"id":"dtd","label":"Drive-to-destination demand"}],"net_conclusion":"Declining for-sale and STR market. All indicators align negatively. The STR licensing ordinance and elevated rates are documented external factors driving the decline.","commentary":"Scenario 2 is the declining mirror of Scenario 1. STR supply growth is a declining signal even as it represents market interest - more listings competing for fewer guests depresses per-property revenue. The drive-to-destination distractor tests whether students import positive factors from prior scenarios not evidenced in this declining data package.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
