l":"STR regulatory risk"},{"id":"new","label":"New construction pipeline"}],"net_conclusion":"Improving for-sale and peak STR market with material seasonal concentration risk and an amenity fee headwind. The consulting narrative must address all three dimensions.","commentary":"Scenario 3 introduces the peak/off-season revenue split. Seasonal concentration is Market-Dependent because its investment impact depends on individual investor assumptions. The amenity fee increase is Declining because it is documented, imminent, and quantifiable. Students must resist classifying the seasonal structure itself as Declining - it is a structural feature of the market, not a directional signal.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
