ry status"},{"id":"seas","label":"Seasonal revenue concentration"},{"id":"amen","label":"Amenity fee"}],"net_conclusion":"Improving for-sale and STR market. STR supply growth is Market-Dependent - growing supply has not yet depressed per-property revenue. No regulatory risk. The lender''s market condition designation: Improving/Increasing.","commentary":"Scenario 4 contrasts with Scenario 2''s declining STR market. The STR supply growth factor is Market-Dependent (not Declining) because revenue per property is still growing despite supply expansion - demand has absorbed the supply increase. Students must avoid automatically classifying supply growth as Declining when the per-property revenue data contradicts that conclusion.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
