"factors":[{"id":"pm_abs","label":"Permanent market absorption rate trend"},{"id":"pm_dom","label":"Permanent market days on market trend"},{"id":"pm_lts","label":"Permanent market list-to-sale ratio"},{"id":"pm_msp","label":"Permanent market price trend"},{"id":"pm_inv","label":"Permanent market inventory level"},{"id":"str_occ","label":"STR peak occupancy trend"},{"id":"str_nr","label":"STR peak nightly rate trend"},{"id":"str_rev","label":"STR gross annual revenue trend"},{"id":"str_off","label":"STR off-season occupancy trend"},{"id":"str_offr","label":"STR off-season nightly rate trend"},{"id":"str_sup","label":"STR supply growth"},{"id":"str_reg","label":"STR regulatory risk"},{"id":"scarcity","label":"Lakefront lot scarcity"},{"id":"ret","label":"Retirement and migration demand driver"},{"id":"seas","label":"Seasonal revenue concentration"},{"id":"lender_des","label":"Lender market condition designation"},{"id":"cap","label":"Cap rate direction"}],"net_conclusion":"Dual-framework analysis. Lender designation: Increasing/Improving - permanent market and STR revenue both improving. Consulting conclusion: improving headline with STR supply growth, regulatory risk, and seasonal concentration as investor-specific risk factors requiring narrative treatment.","commentary":"Scenario 9 runs the mortgage lending and private consulting frameworks simultaneously - a direct parallel to Module 5''s combined VA/SCDOT scenario. The lender Increasing designation is supported by all primary indicators. The consulting conclusion must go further: STR supply growth and regulatory risk are material investor-specific factors the lender framework does not require but the consulting client needs.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
  '{"factors":{"pm_abs":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"5.8 to 3.1 months - crossed from balanced into seller''s territory. Core lender market condition data."},"pm_dom":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"48 to 28 days - demand velocity improving significantly."},"pm_lts":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"97.8 to 100.4% - crossed above asking. Buyer competition confirmed in permanent market."},"pm_msp":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"+7.0% - meaningful appreciation in the permanent lakefront market."},"pm_inv":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"7 to 4 actives - tightening supply reinforcing the improving picture. Lot scarcity amplifies this signal."},"str_occ":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"74 to 79% peak occupancy - strong demand absorption improvement during the primary revenue season."},"str_nr":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"$341 to $389 (+14.1%) - meaningful pricing power improvement during peak season."},"str_rev":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"$54,800 to $67,400 (+23%) - strong revenue growth supporting the STR income thesis."},"str_off":{"present":true,"classification":"Stable","rationale":"29 to 32% - modest off-season improvement but structurally lower than peak. Stable is the appropriate classification."},"str_offr":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"$198 to $211 (+6.6%) - off-season rates improving modestly."},"str_sup":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"37% STR listing growth - each listing now competes against more alternatives, a per-property revenue risk signal even as total market demand grows."},"str_reg":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"Active zoning review with a 4-month vote timeline is material, imminent, and documented. A real risk to the STR income model."},"scarcity":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"Fewer than 6 undeveloped lots remaining - structural supply constraint supporting long-term value appreciation for existing lakefront properties."},"ret":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"Documented, verifiable demand driver for the permanent residential market in the Lake Keowee corridor."},"seas":{"present":true,"classification":"Market-Dependent","rationale":"79% peak vs. 32% off-season occupancy - heavy revenue concentration in 5 months. Investment impact depends on individual cash flow and financing assumptions."},"lender_des":{"present":false,"rationale":"DISTRACTOR: The lender designation (Increasing/Improving) is a conclusion drawn from the indicator analysis - not itself an indicator. Do not include conclusions in the indicator checklist."},"cap":{"present":false,"rationale":"No cap rate data was provided in this package. This is a distractor."}}}'::jsonb
FROM scenarios s
JOIN scenario_categories sc ON sc.id = s.category_id
JOIN module_sections ms ON ms.id = sc.section_id
JOIN section_fields f ON f.section_id = ms.id AND f.field_key = 'market_indicator_analysis'
WHERE sc.code = 'M2-S6-C6'
  AND s.order_index = 9;


